<hr WIDTH="100%">

<h3>Lab Assignment:</h3>

Note: Everything in this lab assignment, unless otherwise stated, must be performed on the appropriate server.

<ol TYPE=I>

    <li>
	Create the directory <code>lab6</code> in your <code>labs</code> directory, then move to it <br>
	(you can use the <code>cd</code> or <code>pushd</code> command in Unix to move to a directory).
    </li>

    <li>
	Perform LAB exercises 6.1 - 6.3 and LAB 6.4 <i>Options</i> 1 &amp; 3.
    </li>

    <li>
	Use your editor to write the answers to the questions and exercises in
	<a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/9e/Labs/PDFs/LM_Chapter06.1_9e.pdf">Lab 6</a>
	in the file <code>Lab6answers.txt</code> locating it in directory <code>lab6</code></li>. <br>
	Then submit the file to your lab 6 Assignment dropbox in D2L.<br>
	As with all assignments submitted to a dropbox, your <u>name</u>, login</u>, <u>assignment category &amp; number</u> [e.g. Lab 6],
	and <u>date</u> must be included at the top of your file.
    </li>

    <li>
    When you are sure that each program is working correctly, use the <code>script</code> command to display first the source file, then execution, 
    of each lab assignment program.<br>
    If the numbered Lab (e.g. Lab 6.2) has multiple exercises, display and run only the final exercise.<br>
    Answer any questions in a separate <code>.txt</code> file. <br><br> 
    The <code><b>^D</b></code> character will end the <code>script</code> session.<br>
    What you enter into your <code>script</code> session will look like this:
    <code>
    <pre>
	&gt;script -a Lab6typescript.txt
	&gt;g++ -o &lt;program1&gt; &lt;program1&gt;.cpp
	&gt;program1
	    (your input to &lt;program1&gt; is here (if any))
	&gt;g++ -o &lt;program2&gt; &lt;program2&gt;.cpp
	&gt;program2
	    (your input to &lt;program2&gt; is here (if any))
	    .
	     .
	      .
	&gt;^D
    </pre>
    </code>
    Submit <code>Lab6typescript.txt</code> to your lab 6 D2L Assignment Dropbox.
    Also, submit to your lab 6 D2L Assignment Dropbox a syntax-highlighted PDF file for each source code that you execute and test in your script session.<br>
    Each PDF file should have the same name as the source file with the exception of the file extension (<code>.gpp</code> &rarr; <code>.pdf</code>).
    </li>

</ol>
Here are the authors' source files for this lab:
<code>
    <ul>
